<subSubSection id="C369651EFF90FFB0FF4CF978FD3A737B" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCC3695FF90FFB0FF4CF978FD3A737B" blockId="0.[151,1436,1428,2020]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FF4CF978FEB472C8" bold="true" box="[198,337,1719,1743]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
A typical member of 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D16FF90FFB0FDCBF977FC9872C8" authority="" authorityName="Gnaspini" authorityYear="1996" box="[577,893,1720,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Appadelopsis">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FDCBF977FD3672C8" box="[577,723,1720,1743]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Ptomaphagus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FD6EF977FC9672C8" box="[740,883,1720,1743]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Appadelopsis</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13482A10FF90FFB0FC07F977FC2972C8" box="[909,972,1720,1743]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1080,1104]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,386,1073]" captionTargetId="figure-192@1.[264,1323,366,1090]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ptomaphagus merritti sp. n. Dorsal habitus of the holotype." pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4C8B9B70FF90FFB0FBFBF977FAEA72C8" box="[1137,1295,1720,1743]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="2.85" metricValueMin="2.75" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="2.8" valueMax="2.85" valueMin="2.75">2.75–2.85 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4C8B9B70FF90FFB0FAEAF977FF1972F6" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.375" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.35" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="1.375" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.35">1.35– 1.40 mm</quantity>
. Pronotum 1.72–1.78 times wider then long, 2.09–2.14 times shorter then elytra. Elytra together 1.23–1.29 times longer then wide. Aedeagus apex is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D16FF90FFB0FC99F932FC5C7313" authority="(Peck)" baseAuthorityName="Peck" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[787,953,1789,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suteri">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FC99F932FC8F7313" box="[787,874,1789,1812]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P.suteri</emphasis>
(Peck)
</taxonomicName>
, with dorsal section upturned into long, wide knob with a distinct depression in the middle (
<figureCitation id="13482A10FF90FFB0FD0AF8EFFD027330" box="[640,743,1824,1847]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–6" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[324,1245,1193,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-198@1.[701,1267,1193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 2–6. Genitalia of Ptomaphagus merritti sp. n. 2—aedeagus, lateral view; 3—apex of median lobe, frontal view; 4—apex of median lobe, dorso-lateral view; 5—spermatheca, dorsal view; 6—spermatheca, lateral view." pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Figs. 2–4</figureCitation>
). Edges of both dorsal and ventral sections in frontal view deeply asymmetrically sinuate (
<figureCitation id="13482A10FF90FFB0FE17F88DFE3B735E" box="[413,478,1858,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–6" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[324,1245,1193,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-198@1.[701,1267,1193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 2–6. Genitalia of Ptomaphagus merritti sp. n. 2—aedeagus, lateral view; 3—apex of median lobe, frontal view; 4—apex of median lobe, dorso-lateral view; 5—spermatheca, dorsal view; 6—spermatheca, lateral view." pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Spermatheca (
<figureCitation id="13482A10FF90FFB0FD01F88DFD0A735E" box="[651,751,1858,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–6" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[324,1245,1193,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-198@1.[701,1267,1193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 2–6. Genitalia of Ptomaphagus merritti sp. n. 2—aedeagus, lateral view; 3—apex of median lobe, frontal view; 4—apex of median lobe, dorso-lateral view; 5—spermatheca, dorsal view; 6—spermatheca, lateral view." pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Figs. 5–6</figureCitation>
) with sharp bend in posterior end, distinctly sinuate central section and anterior crest perpendicular to middle section.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C369651EFF90FFB1FF4CF848FDF6753E" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCC3695FF90FFB1FF4CF848FDF6753E" blockId="0.[151,1436,1428,2020]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,152,313]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FF4CF848FEDE7398" bold="true" box="[198,315,1927,1951]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genitalia, primarily the aedeagus, of 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D16FF90FFB0FC9EF847FC997398" box="[788,892,1928,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merriti">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FC9EF847FC997398" box="[788,892,1928,1951]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. merriti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the genitalia of only one described 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D16FF90FFB0FF1DF865FEC273C6" authorityName="Gnaspini" authorityYear="1996" box="[151,295,1962,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Appadelopsis">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FF1DF865FEC273C6" box="[151,295,1962,1985]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Appadelopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D16FF90FFB0FE02F865FD4773C6" authority="(Peck, 1978)" baseAuthorityName="Peck" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[392,674,1962,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suteri" subGenus="Appadelopsis">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FE02F865FE4573C6" box="[392,416,1962,1985]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FE26F865FE2673C6" box="[428,451,1962,1985]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FE59F865FDF573C6" box="[467,528,1962,1985]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">suteri</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B64FF90FFB0FD94F865FD7F73C6" author="Peck, S. B." box="[542,666,1962,1985]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="355 - 382" refId="ref2231" refString="Peck, S. B. (1978) Systematics and evolution of forest litter Adelopsis in the southern Appalachians (Coleoptera: Leiodidae: Catopinae). Psyche, 85 (4), 355 - 382." type="journal article" year="1978">Peck, 1978</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The sinuate margins of the dorsal and ventral sections of the aedeagus are unique to the new species, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D16FF90FFB0FD85F802FD8C73E3" baseAuthorityName="Peck" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[527,617,1997,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suteri">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF90FFB0FD85F802FD8C73E3" box="[527,617,1997,2020]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. suteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are almost straight. The shape of the apical knob of the aedeagus is slightly different in these species. Spermatheca of 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D16FF91FFB1FD3FFF57FCC474A8" authorityName="Tishechkin" authorityYear="2007" box="[693,801,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merritti">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF91FFB1FD3FFF57FCC474A8" box="[693,801,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">P. merritti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a distinctly sinuate central section and anterior section almost rectangularly attached to it, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D16FF91FFB1FD2BFF75FD1E74D6" baseAuthorityName="Peck" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[673,763,186,209]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suteri">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF91FFB1FD2BFF75FD1E74D6" box="[673,763,186,209]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">P. suteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the spermatheca has a straight middle section and the angle between it and apical section is acute. Also, these species have widely allopatric distributions, with 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D16FF91FFB1FB37FF12FAF174F3" baseAuthorityName="Peck" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[1213,1300,221,244]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suteri">
<emphasis id="B907EA87FF91FFB1FB37FF12FAF174F3" box="[1213,1300,221,244]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">P. suteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in the southern Nantahala Mountains south of GSMNP, an area known for numerous narrow endemics among specialized litterdwelling beetles (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B64FF91FFB1FED9FEEDFE27753E" author="Barr, T. C." box="[339,450,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref1970" refString="Barr, T. C. (1974) The eyeless beetles of the genus Arianops Brendel (Coleoptera, Pselaphidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 154 (1), 1 - 51." type="journal article" year="1974">Barr 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B64FF91FFB1FE47FEEDFDE2753E" author="Barr, T. C." box="[461,519,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" pagination="29 - 75" refId="ref2011" refString="Barr, T. C. (1979) Revision of Appalachian Trechus (Coleoptera: Carabidae). Brimleyana, 2, 29 - 75." type="journal article" year="1979">1979</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
